Class IdPaginator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.arm.mbed.cloud.sdk.common.listing.AbstractPaginator<java.lang.String,IdListResponse,IdPageRequester>
      • com.arm.mbed.cloud.sdk.common.listing.IdPaginator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>, java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String>

    @Preamble(description="ID iterator over an entire result set of a truncated/paginated API operation.")
public class IdPaginator
extends AbstractPaginator<java.lang.String,IdListResponse,IdPageRequester>
    Iterator over all the elements of a list without requiring the developer to create and process all the individual requests. This Paginator should be used as the primary way of listing entities. Paginators can be configured to return only a maximum number of results if existing (i.e. parameter maxResult) or to set the page size in order to tweak underlying http communications (i.e. parameter pageSize).

    Note: This paginator is an iterator over IDs.
